               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa ḫǝmamatihu wa-zenā sǝqlatu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos “Book of the
                     Passion and Story of the Crucifixion of Jesus Christ” (fols. 2ra-54rb) &#xD;
                     I-1) Introduction (fols. 2ra-3rb) &#xD; I-2) Homily for Maggābit (fols.
                     3rb-6vb) &#xD; I-3) Homily for Miyāzyā (entitled Zenā sǝqlatu la-ʾǝgziʾǝnä
                     ʾIyasus Krǝstos “Story of the Crucifixion of Our Lord Jesus Christ”) containing
                     the life of Jesus Christ (fols. 6vb-10vb) and 4 homilies (fols. 11ra-16ra)
                     &#xD; I-4) Homily for Gǝnbot (fols. 16ra-18ra) &#xD; I-5) Homily for Sane
                     (fols.18rb-20ra) &#xD; I-6) Homily for Ḥamle (fols. 20ra-22ra) &#xD; I-7)
                     Homily for Naḥāse (fols. 22ra-26rb) &#xD; I-8) Homily for Maskaram (fols.
                     26rb-28va) &#xD; I-9) Homily for Ṭǝqǝmt (fols. 28va-31va) &#xD; I-10) Homily
                     for Ḫǝdār (fols. 31va-33va) &#xD; I-11) Homily for Taḫśas (fols. 33va-36rb)
                     &#xD; I-12) Homily for Ṭǝrr (fols. 36rb-39va) &#xD; II) Taʾammǝra [tazkāra] motu
                     la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos “Miracles Concerning the Commemoration of the Death of Our
                     Saviour Jesus Christ” containing 4 miracles and a concluding part, for Yakkātit
                     (fols. 39va-54rb) &#xD; III) Gadla Takla Māryām “Vita of Takla Māryām (Mäbʿa
                     Ṣǝyon)” (fols. 54rb-74va) &#xD; IV) Miracles of the Saviour of the World worked
                     by ʾabuna Takla Māryām (fols. 74va-76ra) &#xD; IV-1) How the saint healed a
                     child with the swollen throat (fol. 74va-74vb) (cf. EMML no. 3420, fol. 192b)
                     &#xD; IV-2) How ʾabuna Takla Māryām healed a sick child who was near death
                     (fol. 75ra-75vb) (cf. EMML no. 3420, fol. 193a) &#xD; IV-3) About light that
                     appeared over the dough from which the bread for the commemoration of the
                     Saviour was made (fols. 75vb-76ra) (cf. EMML no. 1779, fol. 71b) &#xD; V)
                     Mastabqʷǝʿ za-masqal “Supplication of the Cross” (fols. 76rb-77vb).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Gadla Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon and Miracles of the Saviour of the World worked by
                        ʾabuna Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon are contained also in Maṣḥafa la-tazkāra Madḫāne ʿĀlam
                        “Book of Commemoration of the Saviour of the World” (s.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmr016">MR-016</ref>and<ref type="mss" corresp="ESfbm004">FBM-004</ref>).</note>
                     <note>- Gadla Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon (<locus target="#54rb">54rb</locus> l.8-74va l.3) is
                        assigned for the month Maggābit, s. <locus target="#54r">54r</locus>: ዘአቡነ፡
                        መብዓ፡ ጽዮን፡ ዘይትነበብ በወርኃ፡ መጋቢት ʻOf ʾabuna Mäbʿa Ṣǝyon is read in the month of
                        Maggābitʼ.</note>
                  </msItem>
